pageContext.claim: “Well, Obama didn't do that. And just so you understand, I'm playing a normalization economy, whereas he’s playing a free economy. It’s easy to make money when you're paying no interest. It’s easy to make money when you're not doing any pay-downs, so you can’t — and despite that, the numbers we have are phenomenal numbers.”
pageContext.analysis: Obama, of course, faced the worst economic crisis since the Great Depression, with unemployment reaching 10 percent. The economy is now basically at full employment. Zero percent interest rates would mean the economy was again in a free fall — presumably not something Trump wants.
